Description: Cone of Ḫww (or Ḫw-wỉ): this roughly shaped cone bears on one side a single line of text cut in good incised signs, which gives the name and titles of the Overseer of Dragomans Khuu. No colour remains.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: B. Porter & R. Moss, 'Topographical Bibliography of Ancient Egyptian Hieroglyphic Texts, Reliefs and Paintings' III (Oxford: Clarendon Press), p. 66; Part 2, p. 311.
Bibliographic references: James 1961 / Hieroglyphic texts from Egyptian stelae, etc. Part 1 (pl.25)
